HEADWORD: drop forge
<hw>drop forge</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a device for making large
forgings, in which a heavy hammer drops onto the metalwork to be forged,
pressing it into a form or anvil underneath, or between dies.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drop hammer, drop press.</syn>
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

